We want to use fork and pull,
Approach 1: Fork + Personal Branching
Each contributor forks the upstream repo to their own GitHub account
Contributors create feature branches within their personal fork
Work happens locally, then each contributor pushes to the fork's feature branch
Pull requests go from fork's branch to upstream's main
MUST DO REGULARLY: sync fork with upstream before starting new work
Pro: More control to each feature branch and main repo: mistakes stay in each contributor space
Con: More commands to manage (fork sync + branch management)
